The paper deals with algorithms for computing quasiperiods, which are related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The evaluation of the algorithms involves analyzing data (cs.DM) and numerical methods (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of quasiperiodicity in real-world data, which falls under the scope of social and information networks (cs.SI).
